result.execSummary:
The defendant Justin R Seefeld was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 2nd Degree Sexual Assault of Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(2).
  • 2nd Degree Sexual Assault of Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

superMiscConds.notes: lf extended supervision is revoked and the defendant will have a mandatory release from prison, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling, assessments, and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent, including an AODA assessment and Sex Offender treatment and shall follow through with all treatment recommendations. 

Defendant shall pay department of corrections supervision fees.

Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety. 

Defendant shall register as a sex offender.

Defendant shall comply with all requirements of sex offender registration. 

Defendant shall obtain and maintain full time employment or full time school status, or a combination of employment and school equal to full time status. 

Defendant shall provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Defendant has the right to request expungement of DNA analysis in writing through the Department of Justice.

Defendant shall have no contact with victims K.H.S. or K.M.C. or their families or residences. 

Defendant shall have no contact with anyone under the age of 18 years old except family members or if the contact is approved by the agent.  There may be incidental contact due to employment only if it is approved by the agent.

Defendant shall not possess or use any device that is capable of accessing the internet unless approved by the agent. 

Defendant shall not possess or use any sexually explicit or pornographic materials.

Defendant Justin R Seefeld not in court. Attorney Jeremy C. Przybyla in court for Justin R Seefeld. No appearance by the State. Victim's father, John H. also appears. Przybyla advises that he recently received the restitution information from the State but has not yet reviewed that with def given his incarceration.
